. The test class name seems a bit long, and maybe line length should max out at 120 characters. I’ll need to check the checkstyle setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MtWUktcbEffXtNOUhqRrFic3|fc_03778d9a5b025910016a020455ae288192be5f2a1d425d0395", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"LineLength|<module name=\\\"Line\" -n config build.gradle tests/src/org.clojure/clojure/1.4.0"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2374, "output": 873, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24751, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778517056488, "responseId": "resp_03778d9a5b025910016a02044143f0819282a861c4ea4ac4c8"}}
